cot:
Let $\ell$ be the perpendicular bisector of segment $AC$.  We note that the points that are closer to $A$ than they are to $C$ are the points that are on the same side of $\ell$ as $A$. [asy]
defaultpen(1);

pair C=(0,0), A=(0,3), B=(4,0);

